headline: Extra Space Storage (EXR): Margin Expansion Reinforces Bullish Narratives Despite Slower Revenue Growth
summary: Extra Space Storage (EXR) reported a net profit margin of 27.7%, up from 24.4% in the prior year, with annual earnings growth of 17.4%, which outpaced its five-year average of 8.9%. Looking ahead, earnings are forecast to grow at 6.49% per year, while revenue growth is expected to slow to just 0.7% annually, lagging well behind the broader US market’s 10.3% rate. With earnings quality described as high and continued margin improvement, investors will be weighing these strong profit numbers...
